-- Greece satisfied that ECB tests leave bank bailout buffer untouched 
-- By Lefteris Papadimas
-- Sun Oct 26, 2014 09:28AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, Oct 26 (Reuters) - Greece's finance minister expressed satisfaction on Sunday that the country's banking system "passed successfully" the ECB's stress tests, noting that Athens still has a buffer of 11.4 billion euros at its bank bailout fund. [ID:L5N0SL09J]

